            <a href="http://php.net/" target="_blank">PHP</a> language and is built on the
            <a href="http://symfony.com/" target="_blank">Symfony Framework</a> with a
            <a href="http://mysql.com/" target="_blank">MySQL</a> database for the backend. While it is currently a very
            static site, my plan is to develop it into something that can easily be used by others as a portfolio
            website. In a sense, it will be a Content Management System that is very specific to developers and their
            portfolio.
        </p>
